HEADWORD: Lophiomys
<hw>Lo*phi"o*mys</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>lofia`</grk> a mane, bristly ridge + <grk>my^s</grk> a
mouse.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A very singular rodent
(<spn>Lophiomys Imhausi</spn>) of Northeastern Africa. It is the only
known representative of a special family (<fam>Lophiomyid⟦ae⟧</fam>),
remarkable for the structure of the skull. It has handlike feet, and the
hair is peculiar in structure and arrangement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lophobranch</ent>⟦br⟧
